        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 6:26PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 625 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Love Valley, or 13 miles north of Statesville,
moving northeast at 20 mph. Other strongs storms were moving towards
Moravian Falls.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
North Wilkesboro...
Elkin...
Wilkesboro...
Fairview...
Yadkinville...
Jonesville...
and Boonville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
